    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given the static-only scope of the regulatory claim and the absence of dynamic loading requirements in the predicate comparison. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and 10% relative difference bounds. The overall credibility evidence package is judged sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending.",
